column11:
  In this paper, we show that bounded weak solutions of the Cauchy problem for
general degenerate parabolic equations of the form
  \begin{equation}
  \notag
  u_t \,+\;
  \mbox{div}\,f(x,t,u)
  \;=\;
  \mbox{div}\,(\;\!|\,u\,|^{\alpha} \, \nabla u \;\!),
  \quad \;\;
  x \in \mathbb{R}^{n}\!\:\!, \; t > 0,
  \end{equation}
  where $ \alpha > 0 \, $ is constant, decrease to zero, under fairly broad
conditions on the advection flux $f$. Besides that, we derive a time decay rate
for these solutions.

column5:
5 pages, 10 figures, submitted as a proceeding of the XV
  International Conference on Topics in Astroparticle and Underground Physics
  for Journal of Physics: Conference Series (JPCS)
